All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AbstractCategory
Abstract class inherited by the category and active ticket list classes.
ActiveTicketList
Class that represents the active tickets within the wolf tickets system.
Category
Category class is used to create category objects within the wolf tickets system.
Group
Group provides the main functionality to the wolf tickets system.
GroupReader
Group reader is used to read groups from files into the wolf tickets system.
GroupWriter
Group writer is used to write groups and their associated tickets and categories to files for saving and sharing.
ISortedList<E extends Comparable<E>>
Interface for a list that keeps objects in sorted order as defined by the Comparable interface.
ISwapList<E>
Interface for a list that changes the position of elements through swap operations.
SortedList<E extends Comparable<E>>
Implements the ISortedList interface.
SwapList<E>
SwapList is an array based list class that stores categories and tickets for use in the wolf tickets system.
Ticket
Ticket class is the main building block of the wolf tickets system.
WolfTicketsGUI
Container for the WolfTickets project that provides the user the ability to interact with groups, ticket lists, and tickets.
